modules.description: This module provides functions to set ID3 metadata tags such as title, artist, album, year, comment, track number, and genre on an MP3 encoder. It operates on the `Lame.encoder` type to embed textual metadata directly into encoded MP3 files. Use this module when writing MP3 files to include standard metadata for media players and libraries.

This module provides functionality to configure MP3 encoder parameters (e.g., sample rate, bitrate, VBR mode), convert audio data from buffers (strings, float arrays, bigarrays), and manage ID3 metadata. It operates on encoder instances and audio data structures, supporting use cases like encoding raw audio streams into MP3 files, embedding metadata tags, and retrieving encoding statistics such as frame counts and encoder delay.
